Samuel P. BROWN, Plaintiff in Error, v. UNITED STATES, Defendant in Error. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. April 3, 1926.) No. 4741. M. H. Myerson, of Jacksonville, Fla., for plaintiff in error. Francis L. Poor, Asst. U. S. Atty., of Jacksonville, Fla., and Chas. L. Redding, Asst. U. S. Atty., of Savannah, Ga.

Before WALKER, BRYAN, and FOSTER, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The order appealed

from is affirmed.
